A [[gas explosion]] in a residential area of [[Rosario, Santa Fe|Rosario]], the third-largest city in Argentina, occurred on August 6, 2013. It was caused by a large gas leak; a nearby building collapsed, and others had a high risk of structural failure. Twenty-two people died, and sixty were injured. Several organizations helped secure the area, search for survivors and aid people who lost their homes. Shortly after the explosion, the time frame for reconstruction was estimated at six months. 

The provincial judiciary, headed by judges Juan Carlos Curto, Javier Beltramone and Patricia Bilotta, launched an investigation of the cause of the explosion. Primary suspects were [[Litoral Gas]] (the natural-gas provider) and an employee who did maintenance work at the building that day. Several public figures sent condolences, and most candidates for the 2013 [[Argentine legislative election, 2013|primary elections]] suspended their political campaigns.

==The event==
The explosion occurred at 9:30 am on Oro<U+00F1>o and Salta Streets, in central Rosario. Initial reports confirmed eight people dead, sixty injured and fifteen missing; eight more deaths were later confirmed.<ref name="explo">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1607985-explosion-edificio-rosario|title= Fuerte explosi<U+00F3>n en un edificio de Rosario: asciende a 12 el n<U+00FA>mero de muertos y hay al menos 60 heridos|trans_title= Strong explosion in Rosario: the bodycount rises to 12 and there are at least 60 injuries|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> The following day yielded twelve victims, ten of whom were identitified.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608306-discrepancias-y-dudas-en-torno-a-la-cantidad-de-muertos-que-dejo-la-explosion-del-edificio-e|title= Discrepancias y dudas en torno a la cantidad de muertos que dej<U+00F3> la explosi<U+00F3>n del edificio en Rosario|trans_title= Disagreements and doubts about the number of deaths left by the explosion of the building in Rosario|language= Spanish|date= August 7, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> A number of people were missing; some were found dead among the debris, while others were rescued.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608630-a-mas-de-40-horas-de-la-explosion-buscan-a-11-desaparecidos-en-rosario|title= A m<U+00E1>s de 40 horas de la explosi<U+00F3>n, buscan a 11 desaparecidos en Rosario|trans_title= More than 40 hours after the explosion, 11 dissapeared people are still being searched for|language= Spanish|author= Valeria Musse|date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> The search for survivors ended on August 13, with twenty-one people confirmed dead.<ref name="veintiuno">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1610126-hallan-tres-cuerpos-mas-y-asciende-a-21-el-numero-de-victimas-en-rosario|title= Hallan tres cuerpos m<U+00E1>s y asciende a 21 el n<U+00FA>mero de v<U+00ED>ctimas en Rosario|trans_title= Three more bodies are found, and the bodycount in Rosario rises to 21|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bord<U+00F3>n|date= August 13, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 11, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/explosion-reanudan-busqueda-desaparecidos_0_973102966.html|title= Encontraron dos cuerpos m<U+00E1>s y son 21 los muertos por la explosi<U+00F3>n|trans_title= Two more bodies were found, the deaths of the explosion are 32|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 12, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> An older woman who was injured died on October 8.<ref name="veintidos"/><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Tragedia-Rosario-muertos-explosion_0_1007899257.html|title= Tragedia de Rosario: son 22 los muertos por la explosi<U+00F3>n|trans_title= Tragedy in Rosario: the deaths of the explosion are 22|language= Spanish|author= Mauro Aguilar|date= October 9, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 25, 2014}}</ref> 

The explosion was caused by a gas leak in a 30-year-old building; it severely damaged a nearby nine-storey apartment building, causing it to collapse.<ref name="explo"/> The mayor of Rosario asked residents to avoid the area due to the risk of further building collapses and to ease the work of disaster-management personnel; the streets were covered by broken glass from damaged buildings.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1607987-las-calles-estan-repletas-de-vidrio-dijo-una-vecina-del-edificio|title= "Las calles est<U+00E1>n repletas de vidrio", dijo una vecina del edificio|trans_title= "The streets are filled of glass", said a neighbor of the building|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 6, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}} </ref> Gas and electricity were immediately disconnected, and the national government sent an [[Argentine Federal Police]] task force to the scene.<ref name="explo"/>

The natural-gas utility, Litoral Gas, immediately began sealing the distribution pipe to the area.<ref name="norec"/> CEMAR (Centro de Especialidades M<U+00E9>dicas Ambulatorias de Rosario)  controlled information about the dead and injured, and tents were prepared for those left homeless.<ref name="yajus" /> Firefighters helped to evacuate people trapped on the upper floors of buildings over adjacent roofs.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608023-el-angustiante-rescate-de-los-afectados-por-la-explosion-en-rosario|title= El angustiante rescate de los afectados por la explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario|trans_title= The sad rescue of the victims of the explosions in Rosario|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 15, 2013}}</ref> Although the building was not destroyed by the explosion, the risk of [[Structural integrity and failure|structural failure]] was high.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608024-un-escape-de-gas-la-causa-del-estallido-ocurrido-en-rosario|title= Un escape de gas, la causa del estallido ocurrido en Rosario|trans_title= A gas leak, the reason of the explosion in Rosario|language= Spanish|author= Juan R. Mascardi|date= August 6, 2013|publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 15, 2013}}</ref>

=={{anchor|Investigations}}Investigation==
Neighbors reported to the press that they smelled a gas leak several hours before the explosion and called [[Litoral Gas]], the natural-gas utility. Company director Jos<U+00E9> Mar<U+00ED>a Gonz<U+00E1>lez said it received no complaints; callers may have dialed the 911 emergency number instead.<ref name="norec">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608004-litoral-gas-dice-que-no-tuvieron-reclamos-en-el-call-center|title= Litoral Gas dice que no tuvieron reclamos en el call center|trans_title= Litoral Gas says they had no requests in the call center|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> It was reported at the later trial that the building had several gas leaks before the explosion.<ref name="imputado">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608598-el-gasista-fue-imputado-por-estrago-culposo-y-esta-muy-comprometido|title= El gasista fue imputado por estrago culposo y est<U+00E1> muy comprometido|trans_title= The gas employee was accused and he's very complicated|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bord<U+00F3>n|date= October 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> 

The provincial judiciary launched an investigation of the circumstances surrounding the explosion.<ref name="yajus">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608062-la-justicia-de-santa-fe-ya-investiga-las-causas-de-la-explosion|title= La Justicia de Santa Fe ya investiga las causas de la explosi<U+00F3>n|trans_title= The Santa Fe judiciary is already investigating the causes of the explosion|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> The prosecution conducted a [[search and seizure]] at Litoral Gas' offices to confirm a lack of costumer complaints about the gas leak.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608095-allanan-las-oficinas-de-litoral-gas-en-rosario|title= La Fiscal<U+00ED>a allan<U+00F3> las oficinas de Litoral Gas en Rosario|trans_title= The prosecution seized the offices of Litoral Gas in Rosario|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> Judge [[Juan Carlos Curto]] ordered the arrest of Carlos Osvaldo Garc<U+00ED>a, an employee of the department responsible for gas service to the area,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608131-ordenan-la-detencion-del-gasista-que-trabajaba-en-el-edificio|title= Ordenan la detenci<U+00F3>n del gasista que trabajaba en el edificio|trans_title=Detention of the gas employee who worked in the apartment building ordered|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> during the night;<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608171-detuvieron-al-gasista-que-trabajaba-en-el-edificio-que-exploto|title= Detuvieron al gasista que trabajaba en el edificio que explot<U+00F3>|trans_title= The gas employee who worked at the exploded building has been detained|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> Garc<U+00ED>a's assistant Pablo Mi<U+00F1>o surrendered to police.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608219-detuvieron-a-dos-gasistas-y-allanaron-litoral-gas|title= Detuvieron a dos gasistas y allanaron Litoral Gas|trans_title= Two gas employees were detained, and Litoral Gas was seized|language= Spanish|date= August 7, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> According to witnesses, one employee fled in a van before the explosion when he realized the severity of the gas leak and another remained in an attempt to evacuate people from the endangered area.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608407-uno-de-los-detenidos-huyo-cuando-vio-la-magnitud-del-escape-de-gas|title= Uno de los detenidos habr<U+00ED>a huido cuando vio la magnitud del escape de gas|trans_title= One of the detained employees may have escaped when he saw the severity of the gas leak|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 7, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> The van belonged to Garc<U+00ED>a,<ref name="imputado" /> who experienced an [[acute stress reaction]] during the trial.<ref name="imputado" /> Curto checked the remnants of the employee's cabin to verify Garc<U+00ED>a's testimony.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608728-un-juez-recorrio-el-edificio-de-la-explosion-para-corroborar-los-dichos-del-gasista|title= Un juez recorri<U+00F3> el edificio de la explosi<U+00F3>n para "corroborar" los dichos del gasista|trans_title= A judge visited the building of the explosion to "check" the sayings of the gas employee|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 24, 2013}}</ref><ref name="cruces">{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Siguen-cruces-empresa-actor-principal_0_971302941.html|title= Siguen los cruces: para el juez, la empresa <U+201C>es un actor principal<U+201D>|trans_title= The discussions continue: for the judge, the firm "is a main actor"|language= Spanish|author= Lucas Aranda|date= August 9, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref>

Prosecutor Graciela Arg<U+00FC>elles said that, according to the investigation, Litoral Gas ignored calls for help from Garc<U+00ED>a (who was not properly trained to manage such a situation). The judge said that documents seized from Litoral Gas might prove the existence of customer complaints about a gas leak.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608841-litoral-gas-mas-comprometida-por-la-explosion-en-rosario|title= Litoral Gas, m<U+00E1>s comprometida por la explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario|trans_title= Litoral Gas, more complicated by the explosion in Rosario|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bord<U+00F3>n|date= August 9, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> Curto thought that the employees might not be the sole responsible parties, and that the liability of Litoral Gas must be investigated as well.<ref name="cruces"/>

Pablo Mi<U+00F1>o was released from prison on [[parole]]; Curto refused to do the same for Garc<U+00ED>a, saying that Mi<U+00F1>o had [[extenuating circumstances]] which Garc<U+00ED>a did not.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1609061-explosion-en-rosario-liberan-al-ayudante-del-gasista|title= Explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario: niegan la excarcelaci<U+00F3>n del gasista y liberaron al ayudante|trans_title= Explosion in Rosario: the parole for the gas employee is refused, but accepted for his assistant|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 9, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> Mi<U+00F1>o's job was to give Garc<U+00ED>a the required tools, not to do the maintenance. He was in the street, watching for the van (which was not properly parked and locked), and did not see Garc<U+00ED>a's work before the explosion. Curto stopped short of pronouncing Mi<U+00F1>o innocent at that early stage.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1609288-el-gasista-seguira-detenido-y-citan-a-declarar-a-los-directivos-de-la-empresa-litoral-gas|title= El gasista seguir<U+00E1> detenido y citan a declarar a los directivos de la empresa Litoral Gas|trans_title= The gas employee will stay under detention and the heads of Litoral Gas will be prosecuted|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bord<U+00F3>n|date= August 10, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref>

As the case expanded beyond his jurisdiction Curto [[Judicial disqualification|recused]] himself from the trial and was replaced by [[Javier Beltramone]],<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1611116-la-tragedia-de-rosario-se-quedo-sin-juez|title= La tragedia de Rosario se qued<U+00F3> sin juez|trans_title= The tragedy in Rosario is left without a judge|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 16, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> who released Garc<U+00ED>a on parole.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1611717-explosion-en-rosario-liberaron-al-gasista|title= Explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario: el juez orden<U+00F3> la liberaci<U+00F3>n del gasista|trans_title= Explosion in Rosario: the judge ordered the liberation of the gas employee|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bord<U+00F3>n|date= August 17, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> Litoral Gas demanded Beltramone's recusal for expressing an opinion about the case to the press.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Apartan-juez-investigaba-tragedia-Rosario_0_1008499637.html|title= Apartan al juez que investigaba la tragedia de Rosario|trans_title= The judge investigating the tragedy in Rosario is demoted|language= Spanish|author= Andr<U+00E9>s Actis|date= October 10, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> The recusal was accepted by the appeals chamber in a 2<U+2013>1 vote, and the case was transferred to [[Patricia Bilotta]].<ref name="Bilotta">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1627802-separan-al-juez-que-estaba-a-cargo-de-la-investigacion-de-la-explosion-en-rosario|title= Separan al juez que estaba a cargo de la investigaci<U+00F3>n de la explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario|trans_title= The judge who was dealing with the investigation of the explosion in Rosario has been removed|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bord<U+00F3>n|date= October 10, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> Garc<U+00ED>a had claimed that he was following instructions received in the previous days, so Bilotta summoned the technical support of Litoral Gas to clarify that point.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/la-ciudad/Salta-2141-Quieren-establecer-si-el-gasista-notifico-a-Litoral-Gas--20131126-0031.html|title= Salta 2141: Quieren establecer si el gasista notific<U+00F3> a Litoral Gas|trans_title= Salta 2141: they want to establish if the gas employee notified Litoral Gas|language= Spanish|author= |date= November 26, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref> Litoral Gas said that Garc<U+00ED>a did not receive any instructions prior to the explosion.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/la-ciudad/Litoral-Gas-dijo-que-el-gasista-no-pidio-permiso-para-proceder-20131127-0032.html|title= Litoral Gas dijo que el gasista no pidi<U+00F3> permiso para proceder|trans_title= Litoral Gas said that the gas employee did not ask for permission to proceed|language= Spanish|author= |date= November 27, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref>

Litoral Gas proposed an [[out-of-court settlement]] to the relatives of the victims, starting from 1,200 dollars for each square meter.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/la-ciudad/Ahora-Litoral-Gas-les-propone-un-arreglo-economico-a-las-victimas-de-Salta-2141-20131129-0041.html|title= Ahora Litoral Gas les propone un arreglo econ<U+00F3>mico a las v<U+00ED>ctimas de Salta 2141|trans_title= Now Litoral Gas proposes an economic agreement to the victims of Salta 2141|language= Spanish|author= |date= November 29, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref> Vice Governor [[Jorge Henn]] rejected is as immoral.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/la-ciudad/El-vicegobernador-Henn-aseguro-que-lo-de-Litoral-Gas-es-inmoral-e-inescrupuloso-20131130-0029.html|title= El vicegobernador Henn asegur<U+00F3> que "lo de Litoral Gas es inmoral e inescrupuloso"|trans_title= Vicegovernor Henn swore that "Litoral Gas' proposal is immoral and unscrupulous"|language= Spanish|author= |date= November 30, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref> The proposal was rejected by most of the accusers.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/la-ciudad/Familiares-de-victimas-de-Salta-2141-rechazan-un-ofrecimiento-economico-de-Litoral-Gas-20131128-0037.html|title= Familiares de v<U+00ED>ctimas de Salta 2141 rechazan un ofrecimiento econ<U+00F3>mico de Litoral Gas|trans_title= Relatives of victims of Salta 2141 reject an economic offering from Litoral Gas|language= Spanish|author= |date= November 28, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref>

=={{anchor|Reactions}}Reaction==
[[File:070813-rosario2.jpg|thumb|left|alt=Woman walking through a disaster area with many other people|President [[Cristina Fern<U+00E1>ndez de Kirchner]] at the site of the explosion]]
The explosion occurred shortly before the primary [[Argentine legislative election, 2013|2013 Argentine legislative elections]] on August 11. The governor of Santa Fe province, [[Antonio Bonfatti]], asked the political parties to end their campaigns to allow mourning for the victims of the explosion.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608063-tras-la-explosion-en-rosario-piden-suspender-la-campana-electoral|title= El gobernador de Santa Fe pidi<U+00F3> suspender la campa<U+00F1>a electoral|trans_title= The governor of Santa Fe asked to suspend the political campaign|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> [[Front for Victory]] and [[Progressive, Civic and Social Front]] candidates suspended their campaigns,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608140-el-frente-para-la-victoria-dio-por-terminada-su-campana-electoral-en-santa-fe-por-la-tragica|title= El Frente para la Victoria dio por terminada su campa<U+00F1>a electoral en Santa Fe por la tr<U+00E1>gica explosi<U+00F3>n|trans_title= The Front for Victory considers their political campaign in Santa Fe ended because of the explosion|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608289-la-tragedia-dejo-en-suspenso-la-campana|title= La tragedia dej<U+00F3> en suspenso la campa<U+00F1>a|trans_title= The tragedy suspended the campaign|language= Spanish|date= August 7, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> and the national government declared two days of [[National day of mourning|mourning]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608358-el-gobierno-declaro-duelo-de-dos-dias-por-la-explosion-de-rosario|title= El Gobierno declar<U+00F3> duelo de dos d<U+00ED>as por la explosi<U+00F3>n de Rosario|trans_title= The government issued a two-days mourning for the explosion in Rosario|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 7, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> The mourning period was observed by all candidates in Buenos Aires and the Buenos Aires and most other provinces, who ended their political campaigns.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608625-sin-actos-el-final-de-la-campana-quedo-tenido-por-la-tragedia-de-rosario|title= Sin actos, el final de la campa<U+00F1>a qued<U+00F3> te<U+00F1>ido por la tragedia de Rosario|trans_title= Without events, the end of the political campaign was stained by the tragedy in Rosario|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> 

President [[Cristina Fern<U+00E1>ndez de Kirchner]], who had recently returned from a diplomatic visit to the United Nations, visited the site of the explosion on August 7. She was berated by local residents;<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608374-cristina-kirchner-llego-a-rosario-para-recorrer-la-zona-de-la-tragica-explosion|title= Cristina Kirchner visit<U+00F3> la zona de la explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario y recibi<U+00F3> insultos de los vecinos|trans_title= Cristina Kirchner visited the area of the explosion in Rosario and received insults from the neighbors|language= Spanish|author= Diego Ya<U+00F1>ez Mart<U+00ED>nez|date= August 7, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> some were angry because her surprise visit halted work at the site, and others thought her presence was politically motivated.<ref name="echada">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608637-insultos-y-abucheos-a-cristina-cuando-visito-el-lugar-de-la-tragedia|title= Insultos y abucheos a Cristina cuando visit<U+00F3> el lugar de la tragedia|trans_title= Insults and booings for Cristina when she visited the place of the tragedy|language= Spanish|author= Valeria Musse|date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> The president stayed briefly, visited the CEMAR and met Bonfatti.<ref name="echada" /> Kirchner's entourage was surrounded by members of [[La C<U+00E1>mpora]], who tried to prevent demonstrations against her and keep journalists and residents at bay.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608558-cruces-entre-militantes-de-la-campora-y-vecinos-por-la-llegada-de-cristina-kirchner-a-rosari|title= Cruces entre militantes de La C<U+00E1>mpora y vecinos por la llegada de Cristina Kirchner a Rosario|trans_title= Clash between militants of La C<U+00E1>mpora and neighbors for the arrival of Cristina Kirchner to Rosario|language= Spanish|author= Diego Ya<U+00F1>ez Mart<U+00ED>nez|date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref>

Several [[social networking sites]] had scheduled a ''[[cacerolazo]]'' (a pot-banging protest demonstration), known as 8A, against Kirchner weeks before the explosion for August 8. The websites had already conducted successful ''cacerolazos'' ([[8N]] and [[18A]]). It went on as planned despite the national mourning, adding the slogan "No more pointless deaths".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608626-el-8-a-sigue-en-pie-con-la-consigna-no-mas-muertes-inutiles|title= El 8-A sigue en pie, con la consigna "no m<U+00E1>s muertes in<U+00FA>tiles"|trans_title= The 8-A still stands, with the slogan "no more pointless deaths"|language= Spanish|author= Mariano Obarrio|date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> Candidate [[Ricardo Gil Lavedra]] thought the ''cacerolazo'' should have been canceled (as the campaigning was),<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608671-ricardo-gil-lavedra-hoy-no-deberia-hacerse-la-protesta-del-8a|title= Ricardo Gil Lavedra: "Hoy no deber<U+00ED>a hacerse la protesta del 8A"|trans_title= Ricardo Gil Lavedra: "The 8A protest should not be made today"|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 23, 2013}}</ref> but fellow candidate [[Rodolfo Terragno]] supported it.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608833-rodolfo-terragno-y-ricardo-gil-lavedra-respaldaron-el-cacerolazo|title= Rodolfo Terragno y Ricardo Gil Lavedra respaldaron el cacerolazo|trans_title= Rodolfo Terragno and Ricardo Gil Lavedra supported the cacerolazo|language= Spanish|author= DyN|date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}} </ref> It was attended by fewer people than previous ones in Buenos Aires and the rest of the country.<ref name="ochoa">{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608973-con-una-protesta-menos-masiva-el-8-a-movilizo-a-los-caceroleros-mas-duros|title= Con una protesta menos masiva, el 8-A moviliz<U+00F3> a los caceroleros m<U+00E1>s duros|trans_title= With a less massive protest, the 8-A movilized the strongest caceroleros|language= Spanish|author= Aurelio Tom<U+00E1>s|date= August 9, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> The demonstration in Rosario was not a ''cacerolazo'', but a silent [[candlelight vigil]] attended by nearly a hundred people.<ref name="ochoa" /> There was a second demonstration in Rosario on August 22, that moved from the [[National Flag Memorial (Argentina)|National Flag Memorial]] to the headquarters of Litoral Gas.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Hoy-hacen-marcha-silencio_0_979102344.html|title= Hoy hacen una marcha del silencio|trans_title= There's a silent demonstration today|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 22, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/contenidos/2013/08/20/noticia_0054.html|title= La mam<U+00E1> de Laguia participar<U+00E1> de la marcha "para pedir justicia"|trans_title= The mother of Laguia will take part in the demonstration "to ask for justice"|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 20, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref>

[[Pope Francis]] mailed condolences to Rosario archbishop [[Jos<U+00E9> Luis Mollaghan]], and the pope's letter was read during a [[mass]] and procession for [[Saint Cajetan]] at [[Plaza 25 de Mayo (Rosario)|Plaza 25 de Mayo]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608341-papa-francisco-rosario-edificio-explosion-mensaje|title= El mensaje del papa Francisco por la tr<U+00E1>gica explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario|trans_title= The message of Pope Francis in relation to the tragic explosion in Rosario|language= Spanish|date= August 7, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 10, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Nuevo-mensaje-Papa-edificar-encuentro_0_970103270.html|title= La tragedia de Rosario, presente en San Cayetano|trans_title= The tragedy of Rosario, present at Saint Cajetan|language= Spanish|author= Emily Vexler|date= August 7, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> [[Newell's Old Boys]] and [[Rosario Central]], two local [[soccer]] teams and rivals in the [[Rosario derby]], organized a charity match for the victims at the [[Estadio Gabino Sosa|Gabino Sosa stadium]],<ref>{{cite web |url= http://canchallena.lanacion.com.ar/1608138-newellls-y-central-codo-a-codo-rosario-se-unio-para-ayudar-a-las-victimas-de-la-explosion|title= Newell's y Central, codo a codo: Rosario se uni<U+00F3> para ayudar a las v<U+00ED>ctimas de la explosi<U+00F3>n|trans_title= Newell's and Central, back to back: Rosario has united to help the victims of the explosion|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> and Rosario native [[Lionel Messi]] provided support.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://canchallena.lanacion.com.ar/1608164-lionel-messi-pone-su-fundacion-a-disposicion-de-las-victimas-de-la-explosion-de-rosario|title= Lionel Messi pone su Fundaci<U+00F3>n a disposici<U+00F3>n de las v<U+00ED>ctimas de la explosi<U+00F3>n de Rosario|trans_title= Lionel Messi puts his institution at the service of the victims of the Rosario explosion|language= Spanish|date= August 6, 2013|work= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=September 7, 2013}}</ref> The charity match collected 120,000 pesos.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/contenidos/2013/08/19/noticia_0058.html|title= Cerca de 120 mil pesos se recaudaron con el partido solidario en el Gabino Sosa|trans_title= Nearly 120 thousand pesos were collected in the charity match at the Gabino Sosa|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 19, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref> Musicians [[Fito P<U+00E1>ez]],<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/contenidos/2013/08/15/noticia_0063.html|title= Fito P<U+00E1>ez anunci<U+00F3> una gira por el pa<U+00ED>s en total beneficio para los damnificados de Rosario|trans_title= Fito P<U+00E1>ez announced a national tour to benefit the dammed in Rosario|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 15, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref> [[Vicentico]], [[Babas<U+00F3>nicos]], [[Las Pelotas]], [[Chaque<U+00F1>o Palavecino]], [[Ciro Pertusi]], [[Lisandro Aristimu<U+00F1>o]], [[Pablo Dacal]] and [[Coki de Bernardis]] performed concerts in several Argentine cities to raise money for the victims.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1610957-fito-paez-y-otros-artistas-saldran-de-gira-para-recaudar-fondos-por-la-explosion-en-rosario|title= Fito P<U+00E1>ez y otros artistas saldr<U+00E1>n de gira para recaudar fondos por la explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario|trans_title= Fito P<U+00E1>ez and other artists will make a tour to collect money for the explosion in Rosario|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 15, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Musica-futbol-ayudar-victimas_0_977302571.html|title= M<U+00FA>sica y f<U+00FA>tbol para ayudar a las v<U+00ED>ctimas|trans_title= Music and soccer to help the victims|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 19, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> Fito P<U+00E1>ez did not attend a general concert on August 19,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/la-ciudad/Fito-Paez-se-excuso-por-no-participar-del-festival-solidario-para-las-victimas-de-la-explosion-20130815-0055.html|title= Fito P<U+00E1>ez se excus<U+00F3> por no participar del festival solidario para las v<U+00ED>ctimas de la explosi<U+00F3>n|trans_title= Fito P<U+00E1>ez declined to take part in the charity concert for the victims of the explosion|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 15, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref> which generated controversy.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/contenidos/2013/08/15/noticia_0061.html|title= Pol<U+00E9>mica en las redes sociales por la ausencia de Fito P<U+00E1>ez en el festival solidario de Rosario|trans_title= Controversy in the networks for the absence of Fito Pa<U+00E9>z from the charity festival in Rosario|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 15, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref>

==Reconstruction==
Antono Bonfatti announced that Santa Fe province would provide financial help to the victims of the explosion. Since most houses in the vicinity of the explosion were damaged, affected families would receive a subsidy of $20,000 to rent homes during reconstruction. They would receive $50,000 in credit to purchase furniture and appliances, payable in 60 months with five percent interest.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1608795-el-gobernador-de-santa-fe-antonio-bonfatti-anuncio-subsidios-el-estado-va-a-estar-presente|title= El gobernador de Santa Fe, Antonio Bonfatti, anunci<U+00F3> subsidios: "El Estado va a estar presente"|trans_title= The governor of Santa Fe, Antonio Bonfatti, announced subsidies: "the state will be present"|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 8, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=October 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Santa-Fe-reparar-todas-casas_0_971302945.html|title= Santa Fe se har<U+00E1> cargo de reparar todas las casas|trans_title= Santa Fe will deal with the repairs of all the houses|language= Spanish|author= Andres Actis|date= August 9, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> Rosario's real-estate firms prepared a list of houses for rent without charging victims their regular fee.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1610254-arman-un-padron-de-viviendas-para-los-afectados-por-la-explosion-en-rosario#|title= Arman un padr<U+00F3>n de viviendas para los afectados por la explosi<U+00F3>n en Rosario|trans_title= A list of housing for victims of the explosion in Rosario has been made|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 13, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> The building may have had cheap insurances, that did not cover the risk of an explosion.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Advierten-edificios-seguro-adecuado_0_971302942.html|title= Advierten que muchos edificios no tienen un seguro adecuado|trans_title= It is warned that many buildings may not have a proper insurance|language= Spanish|author= Mart<U+00ED>n Grosz|date= August 9, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> The cars trapped in an underground parking lot could not be retrieved.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/Tragedia-Rosario-recuperar-quedaron-escombros_0_979102350.html|title= Tragedia de Rosario: no podr<U+00E1>n recuperar los autos que quedaron bajo los escombros|trans_title= Tragedy of Rosario: The cars trapped under the debris can not be retrieved|language= Spanish|author= Andr<U+00E9>s Actis|date= August 22, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref>

Salta Street was closed when the search for survivors ended. Engineers began checking the buildings at [[ground zero]], trying to restore the original layout of the street and demolishing unstable structures.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1610242-rosario-tras-el-rescate-de-las-victimas-comienza-el-trabajo-de-reconstruccion-de-la-calle-sa|title= Rosario: tras el rescate de las v<U+00ED>ctimas, comienza el trabajo de reconstrucci<U+00F3>n de la calle Salta|trans_title= Rosario: After the rescue of the victims, the reconstruction of the Salta street began|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 13, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> Secretary of Public Works Omar Saab said that the two remaining buildings were beyond repair, and required demolition.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1610261-hay-que-demoler-los-dos-edificios-que-quedan-lo-antes-posible-dijo-un-funcionario-del-munici|title= "Hay que demoler los dos edificios que quedan lo antes posible", dijo un funcionario del municipio de Rosario|trans_title= "The two remaining buildings should be demolished as soon as possible", said a politician from Rosario|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bord<U+00F3>n|date= August 13, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref> As a sign of respect, the demolition would not be carried out with explosives.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/reconstruccion-Rosario-demorara-meses_0_974902579.html|title= No usar<U+00E1>n explosivos para demoler los edificios que quedaron en pie|trans_title= No explosives will be used to demolish the buildings that still stand|language= Spanish|author= Mauro Aguilar|date= August 15, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> Secretary of Housing Gustavo Leone estimated that the work would take nearly six months.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1610553-rosario-demandara-seis-meses-reconstruir-la-calle-afectada-por-la-explosion|title= Rosario: demandar<U+00E1> seis meses reconstruir la calle afectada por la explosi<U+00F3>n|trans_title= Rosario: It will take six months to rebuild the street damaged by the explosion|language= Spanish|author= Jos<U+00E9> Bordon|date= August 14, 2013|work= |publisher= La Naci<U+00F3>n|accessdate=November 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/reconstruccion-llevara-meses_0_974302840.html|title= La reconstrucci<U+00F3>n llevar<U+00E1> al menos seis meses|trans_title= Reconstruction will take at least six months|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 14, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> The people was allowed to enter to their destroyed houses on small groups at a time, starting on August 9.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.clarin.com/sociedad/volvieron-casas-pasado-tornado_0_971302944.html|title= Algunos volvieron a sus casas: <U+201C>Es como si hubiese pasado un tornado<U+201D>|trans_title= Some people returned to their houses: "it's as if a tornado has passed"|language= Spanish|author= Carlos Carrion|date= August 9, 2013|work= |publisher= Clar<U+00ED>n|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> The nearby streets began to be reopened on August 13.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/contenidos/2013/08/13/noticia_0044.html|title= Se habilit<U+00F3> hoy el carril de Oro<U+00F1>o hacia el sur, y el tr<U+00E1>nsito por Salta desde Alvear|trans_title= The street from Oro<U+00F1>o to the south was habilitated, as well as the mass transit in Salta from Alvear|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 13, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref>

The [[General Confederation of Labour (Argentina)|CGT]] union signed a deal with the association of factories of Rosario and the government of Rosario to make sure that all the victims of the explosions would keep their jobs.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lacapital.com.ar/contenidos/2013/08/19/noticia_0066.html|title= Acuerdo para resguardar la fuente laboral de los damnificados por la tragedia|trans_title= Agreement to keep the jobs of the victims of the tragedy|language= Spanish|author= |date= August 19, 2013|work= |publisher= La Capital|accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref>

